1
00:00:04,001 --> 00:00:05,583
[LJUBO]
Apparently Zoltan's mountain

2
00:00:05,663 --> 00:00:08,005
range houses
ancient elven ruins,

3
00:00:08,085 --> 00:00:11,298
and that "girl" you seek is in
fact a weapon created there.

4
00:00:11,589 --> 00:00:12,630
Read the report.

5
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:14,422
It has everything
you need to know.

6
00:00:15,513 --> 00:00:17,305
She is not a
threat to humanity,

7
00:00:17,425 --> 00:00:19,217
so our business
here is complete.

8
00:00:19,517 --> 00:00:20,848
We'll return at once.

9
00:00:21,059 --> 00:00:22,180
[VAN]
No, I will not.

10
00:00:22,390 --> 00:00:23,391
Why's that?

11
00:00:23,891 --> 00:00:25,473
You are aware that we must

12
00:00:25,563 --> 00:00:28,066
live as our blessings
tell us to, yes?

13
00:00:28,606 --> 00:00:29,938
Mine tells me to stay.

14
00:00:30,688 --> 00:00:31,689
Hmm.

15
00:00:32,230 --> 00:00:34,652
Far be it from me
to tell you otherwise.

16
00:00:35,113 --> 00:00:36,404
I hope that your blessing will

17
00:00:36,484 --> 00:00:38,326
encourage you to
begin a new journey.

18
00:00:39,077 --> 00:00:40,078
[footsteps fading]

19
00:00:40,829 --> 00:00:42,791
[VAN] My lord has
delivered me a revelation.

20
00:00:43,201 --> 00:00:44,743
A trial that I must overcome.

21
00:00:44,913 --> 00:00:46,124
[LAVENDER]
Trial?

22
00:00:46,375 --> 00:00:47,956
To test my faith, no doubt.

23
00:00:48,547 --> 00:00:51,340
My blessing's impulses, which
have guided me until now...

24
00:00:52,170 --> 00:00:54,463
are utterly silent.

25
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:27,689
[birds chirping]

26
00:02:31,853 --> 00:02:32,814
[sighs]

27
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:34,856
Perfect.

28
00:02:37,659 --> 00:02:40,282
There's something to your
tea that eases the soul, Red.

29
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:42,033
Mighty high praise.

30
00:02:42,284 --> 00:02:44,115
So, how's Van been holding up?

31
00:02:44,456 --> 00:02:45,457
[cawing]

32
00:02:45,827 --> 00:02:47,869
Ever since he came
back from your mission,

33
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:49,251
he's been distant.

34
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:52,624
He locks himself in
his room all day to pray.

35
00:02:53,045 --> 00:02:54,877
He speaks much less now too.

36
00:02:55,047 --> 00:02:56,048
-Huh!
-[sighs]

37
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:59,631
Leaving him to his
own devices is unwise.

38
00:02:59,972 --> 00:03:02,514
Sir Ljubo and I take
turns checking up on him.

39
00:03:03,015 --> 00:03:04,016
[TISSE]
Bad time?

40
00:03:04,436 --> 00:03:06,308
[RIT]
Tisse, is something the matter?

41
00:03:06,729 --> 00:03:08,561
I wanted your
opinion on something.

42
00:03:09,021 --> 00:03:11,233
The Adventurer's Guild
received an urgent request

43
00:03:11,313 --> 00:03:13,486
to search for a missing
child in the forest.

44
00:03:13,606 --> 00:03:15,147
Milady and I would go,

45
00:03:15,237 --> 00:03:17,740
but our hands are tied
as long as Van is here.

46
00:03:18,321 --> 00:03:20,653
Other Adventurer's
aren't interested in taking

47
00:03:20,743 --> 00:03:23,206
the mission because they doubt
there's foul play involved.

48
00:03:23,616 --> 00:03:24,707
What should we do?

49
00:03:24,957 --> 00:03:26,039
[ALBERT]
May I volunteer?

50
00:03:26,369 --> 00:03:27,370
Huh?

51
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,162
-[RED] You sure?
-I am.

52
00:03:29,582 --> 00:03:31,714
-I'll find the child.
-Albert.

53
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:34,167
Adventuring was
what I did best,

54
00:03:34,257 --> 00:03:36,169
and I know my way
around those woods.

55
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,922
Trust me, this won't atone

56
00:03:39,012 --> 00:03:41,264
for my unforgivable
behavior, I know that.

57
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:43,677
I'm doing this to help Zoltan.

58
00:03:43,927 --> 00:03:44,928
It is my home.

59
00:03:45,428 --> 00:03:46,429
Absolutely.

60
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:49,643
And nobody like
me is far from a Hero.

61
00:03:50,273 --> 00:03:53,277
And that's fine, because
traveling alongside Esta

62
00:03:53,987 --> 00:03:55,859
is all I ever want to do.

63
00:03:55,989 --> 00:03:57,401
I am truly lucky.

64
00:03:58,242 --> 00:04:00,194
[ALBERT] From here
on, I want to act in a way

65
00:04:00,284 --> 00:04:02,076
that honors my
place at her side.

66
00:04:02,196 --> 00:04:04,078
Well, you already have.

67
00:04:04,698 --> 00:04:05,699
[both chuckle]

68
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,911
What is it?

69
00:04:07,001 --> 00:04:09,293
Nothing. Just glad
we can trust Albert.

70
00:04:09,663 --> 00:04:12,206
Oh, well, I-I suppose.

71
00:04:12,506 --> 00:04:15,169
All the information we
have at the moment is here.

72
00:04:15,339 --> 00:04:16,711
Good luck, Albert.

73
00:04:16,961 --> 00:04:17,962
Thanks.

74
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:20,424
[birds chirping]

75
00:04:23,427 --> 00:04:24,559
[footsteps approaching]

76
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:33,938
♪

77
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:37,071
[sighs]

78
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:40,655
Ah?

79
00:04:41,036 --> 00:04:42,037
[wine dripping]

80
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:44,990
Waiter, fetch me another.

81
00:04:45,450 --> 00:04:46,791
I'm empty over here.

82
00:04:48,493 --> 00:04:50,996
Sir Ljubo drinking
again, I see.

83
00:04:51,797 --> 00:04:52,798
Of course, I am.

84
00:04:53,378 --> 00:04:55,050
Take a seat and join me.

85
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:57,462
[ESTA] Where's Van?
At the inn?

86
00:04:58,093 --> 00:05:01,467
That boy? No, he ran
off on his own somewhere.

87
00:05:01,927 --> 00:05:02,928
You've lost him?

88
00:05:03,559 --> 00:05:05,010
Last I heard from him,

89
00:05:05,511 --> 00:05:08,514
[LJUBO] he was following up
on a tip about a missing child.

90
00:05:08,724 --> 00:05:10,436
He and Lavender went to search.

91
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:12,478
Huh!

92
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:16,112
Why does that boy resist
the teachings I offer him?

93
00:05:16,692 --> 00:05:18,824
Why does he ignore
everything I say?

94
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:21,777
Dear lord, what's become
of my honorable Hero?

95
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,451
At least he can still be fixed.

96
00:05:25,741 --> 00:05:26,743
Yes.

97
00:05:27,123 --> 00:05:28,334
♪

98
00:05:30,206 --> 00:05:32,128
Was it not the almighty himself

99
00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:35,461
who brought the Hero to
me to be molded and primed?

100
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:38,755
[grunting]

101
00:05:39,095 --> 00:05:40,096
[thudding]

102
00:05:40,216 --> 00:05:42,389
Surprised to run
into an ogre out here.

103
00:05:43,430 --> 00:05:44,431
And the child?

104
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:45,682
♪

105
00:05:47,354 --> 00:05:48,355
[animal growling]

106
00:05:48,555 --> 00:05:49,516
[screaming]

107
00:05:49,606 --> 00:05:50,607
[grunts]

108
00:05:51,688 --> 00:05:52,609
[ALBERT]
Sorry about that.

109
00:05:52,689 --> 00:05:53,690
[groans]

110
00:05:54,271 --> 00:05:55,902
Kurukururu!

111
00:05:56,613 --> 00:05:59,486
-You meanie! Leave him alone!
-Just a scratch!

112
00:05:59,907 --> 00:06:03,370
"Meanie", what a way to greet
the adventurer taking you home.

113
00:06:03,490 --> 00:06:05,282
-Home?
-Yep.

114
00:06:05,372 --> 00:06:07,034
Your parents have
been worried sick,

115
00:06:07,124 --> 00:06:09,036
fearing the worst had happened.

116
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:11,288
Kurukururu's with me.

117
00:06:11,629 --> 00:06:13,751
We were playing
when that ogre came.

118
00:06:14,462 --> 00:06:15,673
You're safe now.

119
00:06:16,253 --> 00:06:18,045
Did your friend here
keep an eye on you?

120
00:06:18,886 --> 00:06:19,797
Uh-huh.

121
00:06:19,887 --> 00:06:21,839
Kurukururu protected me.

122
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:24,392
But there's a
scarier one around.

123
00:06:24,472 --> 00:06:25,893
But they were all afraid.

124
00:06:26,144 --> 00:06:27,095
Of what?

125
00:06:27,185 --> 00:06:28,096
[LAVENDER]
Found her!

126
00:06:28,186 --> 00:06:29,187
Huh?

127
00:06:29,557 --> 00:06:30,518
Hero.

128
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:31,599
How is she?

129
00:06:31,809 --> 00:06:32,810
Faring well.

130
00:06:33,191 --> 00:06:34,352
That is good news then.

131
00:06:35,063 --> 00:06:36,274
[ALBERT]
Something feels off.

132
00:06:37,065 --> 00:06:38,406
It's almost suffocating.

133
00:06:39,317 --> 00:06:41,239
If that's all, I'll
take her home now.

134
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:42,951
Come with me.

135
00:06:43,411 --> 00:06:45,533
[VAN] Not until we slay
the evil at fault.

136
00:06:46,164 --> 00:06:47,996
The ogre?
It's dead.

137
00:06:48,707 --> 00:06:51,289
Didn't that thing lure
the child into the forest?

138
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,211
It must be slain.

139
00:06:54,793 --> 00:06:55,794
Wait!

140
00:06:55,874 --> 00:06:57,966
Calm down and
sheathe your sword, Hero.

141
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,839
This is only a fairy
dragon, not a wicked fiend.

142
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:03,222
A fay being, not
unlike Lavender.

143
00:07:03,512 --> 00:07:04,933
It's completely harmless.

144
00:07:05,434 --> 00:07:07,766
You're using
me to beg for its life?

145
00:07:08,187 --> 00:07:10,639
Albert, you have ten seconds.

146
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:13,562
If you are still in my
way, I will kill you.

147
00:07:13,642 --> 00:07:14,643
Ah!

148
00:07:16,816 --> 00:07:17,737
Leave now!

149
00:07:17,817 --> 00:07:19,108
Run while I hold them off!

150
00:07:19,318 --> 00:07:21,320
-You'll die!
-I said to go!

151
00:07:21,490 --> 00:07:22,491
Ah!

152
00:07:25,404 --> 00:07:27,246
Are you friends with
that fay creature?

153
00:07:28,037 --> 00:07:29,038
I'm not.

154
00:07:29,118 --> 00:07:30,119
I just met it.

155
00:07:30,540 --> 00:07:33,162
And are you confident
you can best me in battle?

156
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:35,915
Not in the least.

157
00:07:36,376 --> 00:07:38,838
So, why stand,
despite the inevitable?

158
00:07:38,918 --> 00:07:40,009
"Why?"

159
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:42,172
That is a great question.

160
00:07:42,302 --> 00:07:44,424
My feet won't stop
shaking, to be honest.

161
00:07:44,844 --> 00:07:45,925
But I won't sit back

162
00:07:46,016 --> 00:07:48,388
and watch while you
take an innocent life, Van.

163
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:51,772
I've no choice
but to stand tall.

164
00:07:52,482 --> 00:07:53,563
What is this feeling?

165
00:07:54,895 --> 00:07:56,186
Something deep down,

166
00:07:56,647 --> 00:08:00,030
feeding my desire to witness
you laid low with one slash.

167
00:08:02,693 --> 00:08:04,324
[screaming]

168
00:08:04,445 --> 00:08:05,446
[breaks]

169
00:08:09,119 --> 00:08:10,120
[thudding]

170
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:12,253
[rattles]

171
00:08:13,544 --> 00:08:14,795
Lavender, find them.

172
00:08:15,206 --> 00:08:16,377
Anything for you.

173
00:08:17,838 --> 00:08:18,839
-[groans]
-Ah?

174
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,512
[groans]

175
00:08:25,806 --> 00:08:26,807
Unhand me.

176
00:08:28,219 --> 00:08:30,311
Don't kill it.

177
00:08:31,022 --> 00:08:33,394
Why make such futile
effort for a mere fay?

178
00:08:33,935 --> 00:08:37,358
I am part of the Hero's party.

179
00:08:37,569 --> 00:08:38,570
And?

180
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:39,861
[sighs]

181
00:08:39,941 --> 00:08:43,575
I wish to act in a
way to honor that.

182
00:08:43,905 --> 00:08:44,866
Unhand me.

183
00:08:44,946 --> 00:08:45,947
♪

184
00:08:48,540 --> 00:08:50,742
Let go, let go, let go.

185
00:08:51,042 --> 00:08:53,165
Let go, let go, let go.

186
00:08:53,335 --> 00:08:55,457
Let go, let go, let go.

187
00:08:56,548 --> 00:08:58,460
Let go, let go, let go.

188
00:08:58,550 --> 00:09:00,052
Let go, let go, let go.

189
00:09:00,132 --> 00:09:01,553
Let go, let go, let go.

190
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,175
Let go, let go, let go.

191
00:09:03,255 --> 00:09:05,177
Let go, let go, let go.

192
00:09:05,257 --> 00:09:07,099
Let go, let go, let go.

193
00:09:07,219 --> 00:09:10,182
Let me go!
I am the one true Hero!

194
00:09:10,512 --> 00:09:12,104
Damn you!

195
00:09:13,896 --> 00:09:14,897
[thudding]

196
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:19,071
[grunts]

197
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:22,194
[rattles]

198
00:09:23,115 --> 00:09:24,116
Van, no!

199
00:09:26,329 --> 00:09:27,330
You fought well.

200
00:09:28,451 --> 00:09:29,452
[ESTA]
Regenerate.

201
00:09:32,125 --> 00:09:34,998
Albert, you are a champion.

202
00:09:35,838 --> 00:09:38,461
I am truly proud to
call you my partner.

203
00:09:41,344 --> 00:09:44,758
Esta, why defend a man
who conspires with the wicked?

204
00:09:44,848 --> 00:09:46,099
-[thudding]
-Ah?

205
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:50,053
Van, do I look like I'm
in the mood to chat?

206
00:09:50,604 --> 00:09:53,767
I am filled with rage!

207
00:09:54,898 --> 00:09:55,899
[groans]

208
00:10:01,905 --> 00:10:02,906
Why?

209
00:10:03,197 --> 00:10:05,319
And to think
I admired you, Esta!

210
00:10:05,619 --> 00:10:07,281
[VAN] Perhaps you've
made a grave mistake.

211
00:10:07,371 --> 00:10:08,372
Ah!

212
00:10:08,532 --> 00:10:10,284
You get away from him!

213
00:10:10,914 --> 00:10:11,915
[thudding]

214
00:10:12,246 --> 00:10:13,247
Ah!

215
00:10:14,078 --> 00:10:16,921
If you're so angry,
stop fighting like a bitch!

216
00:10:17,211 --> 00:10:19,383
And what happened
to you, Lavender?

217
00:10:20,004 --> 00:10:21,425
I thought you were
resolved to never

218
00:10:21,505 --> 00:10:23,257
show Van your unfettered mind.

219
00:10:23,467 --> 00:10:24,588
Shut your mouth!

220
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:27,932
I hated you from the
moment I laid eyes upon you!

221
00:10:29,554 --> 00:10:31,345
Dears, time to cool off.

222
00:10:31,436 --> 00:10:32,437
[water dripping]

223
00:10:34,399 --> 00:10:35,400
Give me a break.

224
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,981
Does a lonely archfay really

225
00:10:37,061 --> 00:10:39,023
think she has the
power to stop me?

226
00:10:39,314 --> 00:10:42,026
Careful, you'll ruin
that cute face of yours.

227
00:10:42,567 --> 00:10:44,449
You are a fairy, are you not?

228
00:10:44,819 --> 00:10:45,990
Just die!

229
00:11:03,338 --> 00:11:05,090
♪

230
00:11:08,133 --> 00:11:09,134
[thudding]

231
00:11:12,017 --> 00:11:13,018
[LAVENDER]
Van!

232
00:11:14,099 --> 00:11:15,100
[groans]

233
00:11:15,811 --> 00:11:16,892
Healing hands.

234
00:11:20,736 --> 00:11:22,948
[Van] The girl is finally
within my reach.

235
00:11:23,779 --> 00:11:25,992
Soon, I'll do it.

236
00:11:30,706 --> 00:11:32,038
♪

237
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,872
Will Mr. Adventurer be okay?

238
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:38,214
His wounds have totally healed.

239
00:11:39,045 --> 00:11:41,047
Might look bad,
but he's just resting.

240
00:11:42,759 --> 00:11:44,380
Thank goodness
the kid made it out.

241
00:11:44,801 --> 00:11:46,222
You did good, Albert.

242
00:11:46,973 --> 00:11:48,635
Do we know when
he might wake up?

243
00:11:49,175 --> 00:11:50,176
[RED]
Anyone's guess.

244
00:11:50,387 --> 00:11:53,179
He pushed himself past
his limits to deal with Van.

245
00:11:53,430 --> 00:11:55,142
Give him some time
and he'll come to.

246
00:11:55,392 --> 00:11:56,393
[ESTA]
Right.

247
00:11:56,563 --> 00:11:58,685
It would have been
worse if you weren't there.

248
00:11:59,186 --> 00:12:00,187
[sighs]

249
00:12:00,317 --> 00:12:01,398
Had a hunch.

250
00:12:01,738 --> 00:12:03,650
Couldn't shake
the peril in the air.

251
00:12:05,032 --> 00:12:06,573
But Van is out of control.

252
00:12:07,494 --> 00:12:10,657
[RUTI] The impulses of the
Hero's blessings are unmatched.

253
00:12:10,908 --> 00:12:13,661
Normally, it wouldn't compel
you to submit to emotion.

254
00:12:14,331 --> 00:12:16,413
Imagine how
aimless he must feel,

255
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:18,295
acting on a vague impulse.

256
00:12:18,415 --> 00:12:20,588
Yeah, I know what
he's going through.

257
00:12:21,298 --> 00:12:23,010
Knowing him, all
the inner turmoil

258
00:12:23,090 --> 00:12:24,712
could be driving him insane.

259
00:12:25,343 --> 00:12:28,055
My goal was to change his
thinking, not cause a meltdown.

260
00:12:28,966 --> 00:12:30,348
This is not your fault.

261
00:12:31,018 --> 00:12:32,099
It is mine.

262
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,312
Mine and those who
traveled with him.

263
00:12:35,063 --> 00:12:36,064
Esta?

264
00:12:37,935 --> 00:12:40,028
Let me go gather my
thoughts alone, Red.

265
00:12:41,069 --> 00:12:42,070
[footsteps fading]

266
00:12:45,363 --> 00:12:47,195
-Big Brother.
-Yeah.

267
00:12:54,122 --> 00:12:55,123
[footsteps approaching]

268
00:12:57,496 --> 00:12:58,877
When I clashed with Van,

269
00:12:59,418 --> 00:13:02,050
for the first time in my
life, my anger took over.

270
00:13:03,171 --> 00:13:05,464
Just seeing Albert on
the verge of death, I...

271
00:13:05,844 --> 00:13:07,636
You couldn't hold
yourself back, right?

272
00:13:08,136 --> 00:13:09,308
[ESTA]
I was terrified.

273
00:13:09,928 --> 00:13:11,680
So, terrified of losing him.

274
00:13:12,561 --> 00:13:15,564
Very thought drives a stake
into my heart even now.

275
00:13:16,895 --> 00:13:18,898
Remember when I
tried to lay you low

276
00:13:19,228 --> 00:13:21,270
to keep Rudy
fighting as our Hero?

277
00:13:21,941 --> 00:13:24,984
I've changed so much
since, and it scares me.

278
00:13:25,985 --> 00:13:28,698
One of these days I could
make a devastating choice.

279
00:13:29,328 --> 00:13:30,660
I may lose myself again

280
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:33,162
and do something
beyond repair or apology.

281
00:13:34,373 --> 00:13:35,495
It frightens me.

282
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:38,958
Are you going to cast
aside your feelings for him?

283
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,921
Ah!

284
00:13:45,595 --> 00:13:46,596
No!

285
00:13:47,847 --> 00:13:49,139
I can't do that.

286
00:13:51,051 --> 00:13:52,352
I don't want to.

287
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:54,554
[RED]
Then don't, Esta.

288
00:13:55,805 --> 00:13:58,058
Those emotions don't
come from your blessing,

289
00:13:58,438 --> 00:13:59,980
but from deep
within your heart.

290
00:14:00,861 --> 00:14:03,403
And I think that's really
worth something special.

291
00:14:05,235 --> 00:14:08,158
[ESTA] Emotions that have
nothing to do with our blessings?

292
00:14:08,699 --> 00:14:09,700
[chuckles]

293
00:14:10,951 --> 00:14:12,413
One thing is for certain.

294
00:14:12,953 --> 00:14:14,575
Meeting you people
has turned me

295
00:14:14,665 --> 00:14:16,497
into a terrible woman of faith.
[Red chuckles]

296
00:14:16,707 --> 00:14:17,828
[RIT] Red!
Esta!

297
00:14:18,289 --> 00:14:19,290
[footsteps approaching]

298
00:14:33,394 --> 00:14:34,395
[knocking]

299
00:14:34,555 --> 00:14:35,556
Who's there?

300
00:14:36,227 --> 00:14:37,899
[VAN]
Do you have a moment, Cardinal?

301
00:14:38,269 --> 00:14:39,310
Van, my boy.

302
00:14:39,901 --> 00:14:41,813
Don't be shy.
Door's open.

303
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:43,234
[door opens and creaks]

304
00:14:44,275 --> 00:14:47,238
I am here to inform you
that I'm leaving Zoltan.

305
00:14:48,069 --> 00:14:49,110
Is that so?

306
00:14:49,531 --> 00:14:51,072
You've finally
come to understand.

307
00:14:51,573 --> 00:14:53,204
Then let us prepare to depart.

308
00:14:53,455 --> 00:14:56,037
Before that, I will make
for Undine's abode.

309
00:14:56,117 --> 00:14:57,118
Undine?

310
00:14:57,419 --> 00:14:59,621
[VAN] And I will
slaughter every last fay.

311
00:14:59,711 --> 00:15:01,713
Esta, Gideon,
and everyone else

312
00:15:01,793 --> 00:15:03,215
there will meet the same fate.

313
00:15:03,465 --> 00:15:05,177
Are you mad?
Honestly-

314
00:15:05,257 --> 00:15:06,258
Argh!

315
00:15:06,508 --> 00:15:08,260
Surely that will lure the girl,

316
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:09,932
and then I will kill her, too.

317
00:15:10,552 --> 00:15:13,635
If she hides, destroying
Zoltan should draw her out.

318
00:15:13,976 --> 00:15:15,688
Oh, listen to this no longer.

319
00:15:15,888 --> 00:15:17,439
You are the Almighty's chosen.

320
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:20,022
Now, act as such and
control yourself, Hero-

321
00:15:20,102 --> 00:15:21,103
[groans]

322
00:15:23,736 --> 00:15:24,737
Van.

323
00:15:24,857 --> 00:15:26,489
[grunts]
Why?

324
00:15:26,949 --> 00:15:27,950
[thudding]

325
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:30,823
The whisper of the
Hero's Blessing is no more.

326
00:15:31,494 --> 00:15:34,907
With impulses silenced,
my Blessing is out of reach.

327
00:15:35,408 --> 00:15:39,001
As such, I shall execute
the final urge I was given.

328
00:15:39,252 --> 00:15:42,415
Starting with her, the
girl who bested me will fall,

329
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:43,666
and so will evil.

330
00:15:43,917 --> 00:15:45,758
[footsteps fading]
Wait!

331
00:15:45,838 --> 00:15:46,799
[grunts]

332
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:47,881
[sighs]

333
00:15:48,471 --> 00:15:50,093
♪

334
00:15:53,386 --> 00:15:54,387
[water gurgling]

335
00:15:54,557 --> 00:15:55,599
[RED]
Van's on his way.

336
00:15:56,389 --> 00:15:58,271
And Lavender will
no doubt be with him.

337
00:15:58,932 --> 00:16:01,815
Even with my power, I
cannot stop her alone.

338
00:16:02,235 --> 00:16:04,488
She's even stronger
than a water archfay?

339
00:16:05,108 --> 00:16:07,491
Can you tell us exactly
what we're up against?

340
00:16:08,282 --> 00:16:09,403
Despite everything,

341
00:16:09,493 --> 00:16:11,745
it was not my intent
to out one of my kind.

342
00:16:12,246 --> 00:16:14,658
Suppose it's far
too late for secrets.

343
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:19,703
[UNDINE] The being you call
Lavender is a calamity.

344
00:16:19,793 --> 00:16:20,794
[RIT]
No way!

345
00:16:21,005 --> 00:16:23,667
[UNDINE] Yes, she is
one of the archfay-Ketu,

346
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:26,170
avatars of power
and destruction,

347
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,262
inviting catastrophic disasters

348
00:16:28,342 --> 00:16:30,554
since the time of
this planet's creation.

349
00:16:31,135 --> 00:16:33,017
As civilization advanced,

350
00:16:33,217 --> 00:16:35,720
the ancient elves and
dragons wiped out the Ketu,

351
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:37,562
leaving her the sole survivor.

352
00:16:38,222 --> 00:16:39,474
It was my belief she had

353
00:16:39,564 --> 00:16:41,185
sequestered herself
within a jungle.

354
00:16:41,976 --> 00:16:43,728
Okay, so we've
barreled right past

355
00:16:43,818 --> 00:16:46,030
legendary and
straight into mythical.

356
00:16:46,190 --> 00:16:47,822
Any thoughts on a strategy?

357
00:16:48,193 --> 00:16:50,405
A mythical archfay and
the ultimate champion

358
00:16:50,485 --> 00:16:52,657
of mankind are on
their way as we speak.

359
00:16:52,947 --> 00:16:54,659
No choice but to talk this out.

360
00:16:54,829 --> 00:16:56,041
It's now or never.

361
00:16:56,241 --> 00:16:57,492
Talk this out?

362
00:16:57,792 --> 00:16:59,834
You don't seriously
believe that, do you?

363
00:16:59,955 --> 00:17:01,997
It's gonna come to
blows at some point.

364
00:17:02,838 --> 00:17:05,300
And whenever that
happens, we'll be ready.

365
00:17:05,801 --> 00:17:08,213
Ready to talk down
an out of control Hero?

366
00:17:08,303 --> 00:17:09,304
Yes.

367
00:17:09,384 --> 00:17:10,505
Just think about it.

368
00:17:11,056 --> 00:17:13,058
The unwavering
Hero we knew before

369
00:17:13,969 --> 00:17:16,141
is now second
guessing his resolve.

370
00:17:16,562 --> 00:17:18,894
Give me some time
and I can convince him.

371
00:17:19,264 --> 00:17:20,896
Trust in Red, like I do.

372
00:17:21,317 --> 00:17:23,439
And I'll back him up
if it comes down to it.

373
00:17:23,819 --> 00:17:26,272
So please, let him
handle this, Tisse.

374
00:17:26,902 --> 00:17:29,024
Guess, I'm in
if you two insist.

375
00:17:29,365 --> 00:17:30,366
All right, shoot.

376
00:17:30,486 --> 00:17:32,448
What crazy idea do
you have in store?

377
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:35,781
I'm gonna settle things
one on one with Van.

378
00:17:36,032 --> 00:17:37,994
You want to fight
him all by yourself?

379
00:17:38,414 --> 00:17:39,876
Sounds crazy, all right.

380
00:17:40,286 --> 00:17:41,457
Maybe a little bit.

381
00:17:41,587 --> 00:17:43,209
Anything could
happen, you know.

382
00:17:43,499 --> 00:17:47,924
Call me crazy or just plain
stupid, but think I'll win.

383
00:17:48,504 --> 00:17:50,176
♪

384
00:17:51,798 --> 00:17:52,969
If all is decided,

385
00:17:53,049 --> 00:17:55,512
I shall create a barrier
to minimize damage.

386
00:17:55,602 --> 00:17:57,554
Would any of
you be willing to help?

387
00:17:57,974 --> 00:17:59,185
More than happy to help.

388
00:17:59,556 --> 00:18:01,107
I can lend a hand as well.

389
00:18:01,688 --> 00:18:04,441
[UNDINE] Now, if there's someone
who can defend the village...

390
00:18:04,521 --> 00:18:07,274
Don't worry, Mr. Crawly Wally
and I are on it.

391
00:18:07,364 --> 00:18:08,365
[creature agrees]

392
00:18:08,485 --> 00:18:10,277
Okay, looks like we're set.

393
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:12,409
Give it your all out there.

394
00:18:12,990 --> 00:18:14,161
[ALL]
Alright!

395
00:18:15,783 --> 00:18:16,784
[footsteps approaching]

396
00:18:19,456 --> 00:18:20,457
[water waves crashing]

397
00:18:22,169 --> 00:18:23,330
One more thing.

398
00:18:25,002 --> 00:18:26,083
For good luck.

399
00:18:30,428 --> 00:18:31,589
Thanks, Ruti.

400
00:18:31,719 --> 00:18:32,720
[chuckles]

401
00:18:33,551 --> 00:18:35,052
At long last...

402
00:18:35,803 --> 00:18:38,846
I can reclaim my title
right after I kill you.

403
00:18:44,312 --> 00:18:45,313
[water gurgling]

404
00:18:58,747 --> 00:19:01,369
Be honest,
I will know if you lie

405
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:04,583
[Van]
she is the Hero, Ruti, yes?

406
00:19:05,504 --> 00:19:08,507
This is my destiny set
forth by Lord Demis.

407
00:19:09,378 --> 00:19:11,380
And in order to
fulfill that destiny,

408
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,882
I must first
slaughter that girl.

409
00:19:14,593 --> 00:19:17,136
And when I inherit
the obsolete Hero's power,

410
00:19:17,516 --> 00:19:19,848
I will save the
world as the true Hero.

411
00:19:20,189 --> 00:19:21,310
[RED]
That's stretching it.

412
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,441
Ah!

413
00:19:22,771 --> 00:19:25,144
You don't know what to
do with yourself anymore.

414
00:19:25,694 --> 00:19:28,647
It's sad watching you create
meaning where there is none.

415
00:19:29,068 --> 00:19:30,239
You are mistaken.

416
00:19:30,449 --> 00:19:31,610
[RED]
Am I though?

417
00:19:31,781 --> 00:19:33,653
What's your Hero's
Blessing telling you?

418
00:19:33,783 --> 00:19:35,865
To slaughter the obsolete Hero!

419
00:19:36,495 --> 00:19:39,158
Could it be that you
don't feel anything at all?

420
00:19:39,789 --> 00:19:41,210
[gasps]
[grunts]

421
00:19:41,831 --> 00:19:43,623
What have you done
to me, Guide bearer?

422
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:46,045
Do you know
how painful this is?

423
00:19:46,466 --> 00:19:49,128
To feel doubts creeping
in, clouding your inner voice?

424
00:19:49,549 --> 00:19:51,010
Everyone doubts themselves.

425
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:52,472
It's just a fact of life.

426
00:19:52,592 --> 00:19:54,174
The Hero is above that!

427
00:19:54,344 --> 00:19:56,176
I refuse to accept this!

428
00:19:56,306 --> 00:19:57,977
[RUTI]
I did, so why can't you?

429
00:19:58,308 --> 00:20:00,060
Accepted it over and over,

430
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,811
while fighting the army.

431
00:20:02,432 --> 00:20:04,524
The entire time I was afraid.

432
00:20:04,815 --> 00:20:08,108
Asking myself every day if
what I did was right or wrong.

433
00:20:09,609 --> 00:20:11,531
And after my
brother left the party,

434
00:20:11,902 --> 00:20:13,243
those feelings worsened.

435
00:20:13,824 --> 00:20:15,746
Until I didn't know
what to think anymore.

436
00:20:16,246 --> 00:20:18,158
At some point,
I shut myself off

437
00:20:18,248 --> 00:20:19,830
from the people I could trust.

438
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:22,413
And yet, they're
helping me out now.

439
00:20:22,873 --> 00:20:24,295
After all this time,

440
00:20:25,836 --> 00:20:26,877
look at us now.

441
00:20:27,007 --> 00:20:28,669
We've become an actual party.

442
00:20:29,710 --> 00:20:30,671
Shut up!

443
00:20:30,761 --> 00:20:32,963
A true Hero would
never waver from the role

444
00:20:33,054 --> 00:20:34,805
assigned to him by the
almighty Lord Demis!

445
00:20:34,885 --> 00:20:36,137
Quit running, Van!

446
00:20:36,387 --> 00:20:37,348
Urgh!

447
00:20:37,518 --> 00:20:39,310
If being the Hero is
what you want,

448
00:20:39,390 --> 00:20:41,312
quit running from
the doubts you have.

449
00:20:41,682 --> 00:20:43,434
Face them head on courageously.

450
00:20:43,644 --> 00:20:44,726
Confront it?

451
00:20:44,816 --> 00:20:45,727
That's right.

452
00:20:45,817 --> 00:20:47,779
No matter how
painful things might get,

453
00:20:47,939 --> 00:20:50,231
stand firm and
walk your own path.

454
00:20:50,401 --> 00:20:51,983
That's what you call courage.

455
00:20:52,574 --> 00:20:54,906
[VAN] A Hero is
completely immune to fear.

456
00:20:55,196 --> 00:20:56,448
That alone is good enough.

457
00:20:57,158 --> 00:20:58,289
[RED]
And as the Guide...

458
00:20:58,740 --> 00:21:00,582
my job is to show you the way.

459
00:21:01,953 --> 00:21:02,954
[thudding]

460
00:21:03,335 --> 00:21:04,336
So, fight me.

461
00:21:04,416 --> 00:21:05,377
With that sword.

462
00:21:05,457 --> 00:21:06,458
Ugh!

463
00:21:06,548 --> 00:21:07,799
[VAN]
The Bronze Blade?

464
00:21:08,049 --> 00:21:10,342
[RED] This is a battle between
the Hero and the Guide.

465
00:21:10,882 --> 00:21:12,844
Strike me down
where I stand, Van.

466
00:21:13,425 --> 00:21:15,347
Do that and you'll
find your answer.

467
00:21:21,683 --> 00:21:22,765
[VAN]
Very well.

468
00:21:23,565 --> 00:21:25,317
Don't listen to that liar, Van!

469
00:21:25,728 --> 00:21:27,149
Not another inch from you.

470
00:21:27,229 --> 00:21:28,901
Move or die, Rit!

471
00:21:29,071 --> 00:21:30,112
You heard what he said.

472
00:21:30,192 --> 00:21:32,234
This is between Hero and Guide.

473
00:21:32,324 --> 00:21:33,826
I'll tear out your tongue.

474
00:21:33,906 --> 00:21:36,449
Any fool who gets
between me and my beloved

475
00:21:36,619 --> 00:21:38,621
will beg for death
when I'm through!

476
00:21:38,701 --> 00:21:41,204
Say what you will,
but my love is fighting too.

477
00:21:41,664 --> 00:21:43,956
And I won't tolerate
anyone threatening him.

478
00:21:44,287 --> 00:21:47,380
Fay, the Hero, even
the Almighty Demis.

479
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:49,502
And if you try
to interfere, you'll die.

480
00:21:50,503 --> 00:21:51,424
♪

481
00:21:51,504 --> 00:21:53,546
We stop our swords
at the last moment.

482
00:21:53,927 --> 00:21:56,719
And the loser
will admit defeat.

483
00:21:56,890 --> 00:21:58,301
Is that the outcome you wish?

484
00:21:58,391 --> 00:21:59,392
Not today.

485
00:21:59,683 --> 00:22:01,554
This ends when
one of us goes down.

486
00:22:01,645 --> 00:22:02,686
A real fight.

487
00:22:03,266 --> 00:22:04,477
"A real fight?"

488
00:22:04,768 --> 00:22:06,359
Good, because I won't stop

489
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:09,192
until I unleash
this rage upon you!

